{"title":"Cascade Components offer progressive, longer travel link for the Norco Optic","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/21/cascade-components-offer-progressive-longer-travel-link-for-the-norco-optic/","date":1634826897000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"cascade components custom link norco optic boosts travel 130mm\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102131/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-aftermarket-swap.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-275575\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Cascade Components has CNC machined an aftermarket link for the Norco Optic short-travel trail bike. Increasing progression from 17% to 23%, it concomitantly increases travel by 5mm taking it up to 130mm. So, how does that change the rear end’s behaviour, and does it require a longer stroke shock?</p><h2>Cascade Components Norco Optic Link</h2><div id=\"attachment_229672\"><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-229672\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review.jpg\" alt=\"norco-optic-review\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review-696x464.jpg 696w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/norco-optic-review-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-229672\">Our tester, Rob Hinds, putting the Norco Optic C3 through its paces on the stock link that delivers 125mm travel; full review <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/20/review-the-norco-optic-c3-is-an-intuitive-lean-shred-machine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a></p></div><p>Like many of Cascade Components’ aftermarket links, the link for the Norco Optic gives the rear a higher starting leverage ratio, making the suspension feel softer off the top of the stroke. On the trail, the increased overall progression, boosted from 17% to 23%, is said to provide better traction and small bump compliance while simultaneously making the bike harder to bottom out.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock.jpg\" alt=\"cascade components norco optic link leverage ratio graph versus stock link\" width=\"1600\" height=\"890\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-297x165.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-800x445.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-120x67.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-768x427.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21102135/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1536x854.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>No, it doesn’t require a shock swap; it requires the same 190mm x 45mm shock that comes stock on the Norco Optic frames. This is simply a straight swap of the stock link for Cascade Components’ aftermarket link. It can be done at home with the use of basic tools, and is said to take around 20 minutes.</p><p><em>“Although we tend to focus more on descending, we recognize that the Optic is still a trail bike.&nbsp; Because a trail bike needs to be able to climb well, we made sure to maintain the excellent pedaling characteristics of the Optic so you can still take the bike on the longest rides imaginable” – </em>Cascade Components.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><div id=\"attachment_275696\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275696\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1.jpg\" alt=\"cascade components custom link increased progression longer travel 130mm link\" width=\"1600\" height=\"533\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1-297x99.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1-800x267.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1-120x40.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1-768x256.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21103017/cascade-components-norco-optic-link-progression-graph-versus-stock-1-1536x512.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275696\">The Cascade Components Norco Optic custom link is CNC’d from 6061-T6 aluminium in the USA; it weighs a claimed 255g</p></div><p>The Cascade Components Norco Optic link is available now, retailing at $332 USD. When you buy one of these, you’re also buying fresh Enduro Bearings, already pressed into their housings.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://cascadecomponents.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>CascadeComponents.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a50ebfeffcfd35f31d6306a5f44b0c086961108a17734fff42f34600d2bbef7e","category":"Cycling"}